		"reset": "Z-Wave Factory reset procedureThe 2KLIC controller has an option to factory reset which allows the system to return back to its default settings, the steps are given below:From the home page, click on the propertyClick the System status icon in the left menuClick the Smart controller card, which is the first card visible, to edit the smart controller settingsGo to the Manage Z-Wave tab Open the Advanced optionsFind the Reset cardClick on the Reset button to startClick on the text input and type 'Confirm' in the box belowThen click on the Confirm buttonYou will see \"The controller is resetting. Please wait. It could take up to 1 minute.\" messageAnd then you will see \"The controller has been reset\", as soon as it is done resettingNow you have to start adding new devices to your controller and take all the necessary steps to get your system up and running.Resetting this controller will leave your Z-Wave devices orphaned in the network. Please remove all Z-Wave devices before performing this reset procedure. If this controller is a part of another Z-Wave network, please use this procedure only in the event that the network primary controller is missing or otherwise inoperable."
